headline: WEC Energy Group (NYSE:WEC) Projects 2025 Earnings Growth and Announces Dividend Increase
summary: WEC Energy Group has recently provided earning guidance for 2025, projecting earnings between $5.17 and $5.27 per share, with a midpoint of $5.22. In addition, the company plans to increase its quarterly dividend to 89.25 cents per share in the first quarter of 2025, marking a 6.9% rise. These developments, alongside a robust capital plan and strategic investments in renewables, underscore WEC's growth potential despite challenges such as regulatory changes and financial constraints.
